description:
Role purpose
The Software Developer will be part of the core development team, which will have the responsibility for supporting and enhancing current information systems at MAP Life. Utilizing a Software Development Life Cycle, the Software developer will work with technical and non-technical associated in defining business and technical requirements to develop new functions or redesign/consolidate existing processes.

Key Accountabilities 
This position will be mainly responsible for following:
-	Take part in specific developments for core application, new insurance products and configurations;
-	Develop new tools and functions for existing applications to improve end-user support quality;
-	Creates and executes designs for small sets of new functionality as part of a software project;
-	Work with team in building web services and web based applications;
-	Work with partners to develop and maintain communication between software systems;
-	Build new reports and enhance existing ones as requested by internal business groups. Further enhance other reporting technologies to improve performance and scalability of user demand;
-	Day to day maintenance and support of all existing applications in use at MAP Life; 
-	Fill in where needed on the development side to ensure daily operations at MAP Life run smooth without any interruption; 
-	Take part in creating, modifying IT processes when required;
-	Performs other duties as assigned by management.

requirements:
-	Three years of experience in Java, C++ development;
-	Experience in building applications using web services;
-	Proficiency in SQL development mainly on MySQL, Microsoft SQL Server and Oracle database platform; 
-	Working knowledge of PL/SQL and development in Oracle databases; 
-	Experience working with source control systems; 
-	Complete understanding of application development life cycle;
-	Good problem solving skills is a big bonus;
-	Experience working in life insurance companies or software projects is a big bonus;
-	Ability to accurately collect requirements and estimating the efforts involved; 
-	Ability to independently work on projects and finish them within time and budget;
-	Ability to effectively manage time while working on multiple assignments with guidance as to relative priorities of assignments.

